article.headline: Southern Miss 78, Auburn 60
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Brandon Robinson scored 20 points and Marco Killingsworth added 16 to lead Auburn to a 78-60 victory over Southern Mississippi Tuesday night. Troy Gaines added 11 points for the Auburn (8-2). Kyle Davis grabbed a season-high 13 rebounds for the Tigers, who dominated the boards 40-25. Clement Carter led the Golden Eagles (6-4) with 21 points, while David Haywood added 14 points. The Golden Eagles led 31-30 at halftime, but lost their lead after 10-0 run by Auburn in the starting minutes of the second half. Robinson made a pair of 3-pointers to help the Tigers make a 29-6 run, giving Auburn a 59-37 lead with 9:32 remaining. Carter hit four 3-pointers in less than three minutes to cut the deficit to seven, but Southern Miss didn't get any closer. The Tigers outscored Southern Miss 40-18 in the paint, and gathered 24 points off the Golden Eagles' 17 turnovers. Auburn has won 11 straight games in the Southern Miss Series.
